(14, 11, 'BEST OF KENYA â€“ 6DAYS / 5NIGHTS', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '2011-10-15 09:02:18', '131554837125376.JPG', '<p>\r\n	Day 1</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Met on arrival at Jomo Kenyatta International airport by Erdemann Safari Guides.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Briefing by our Chinese Speaking Guide.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Drive southwards through the lush Kapiti Plains to the slopes of Mt. Kilimamjaro (5985M) to arrive at Amboseli National Park in time for lunch.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	1530hrs Afternoon game viewing drive in the park tucked on the vistas of the snow capped Mt Kilimanjaro.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Dinner and overnight at SENTRIM TENTED CAMP (FB).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(Mt Kilimanjaro at 5985m above sea level, is the highest point in Africa. Initially in Kenya, the Mountain was given out as a birthday present to a Tanzanian princess.)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Day 2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	0730hrs. Breakfast at the camp, drive northwards to the Central Highlands of Kenya.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Arrive in time for lunch at Outspan Hotel.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	1530hrs. You will be transferred in lodge vehicles to the Treetops Hotel.Viewing of wildlife from the safety of your balcony.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Dinner and overnight at the TREETOPS HOTEL (FB)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(Tucked deep into the Aberdare Forest the lodge is world famous for in April of 1952, a young princess ascended the same hotel for an overnight stay, to descend the following day as Queen Elizabeth II of England)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Day 3 &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Breakfast at the Treetops. Descend to the Outspan Hotel and rejoin our Driver guide.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Drive over the Aberdare Ranges to cross over the Equator. Proceed via the Thomson Falls to descend into the Great Rift Valley.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Arrive in time for lunch at Lake Nakuru National Park.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	1530hrs Afternoon game viewing drive along the shores of the lake dotted pink by a myriad of lesser flamingoes. Lake Nakuru National park is also a sanctuary for the White Rhino.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Dinner and overnight at LION HILL LODGE (FB)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(The Rift Valley formed about 2m years ago is about 8500kms long and extends from Botswana in the Southern Africa to Iraq in the Middle East). It hosts 8 lakes across Kenya.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Day 4 &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	0730hrs &ndash; After breakfast at the lodge, depart and drive across the floor of the Rift Valley past Lake Elementaita, Lake Naivasha and Mt. Longonot to the County of the Maasai People.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Arrive at the world famous Maasai Mara Game reserve in time for lunch.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	1600hrs Afternoon game viewing drive in the expansive grasslands with a high concentration of wildlife.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Dinner and overnight at SAROVA MARA CAMP (FB)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Day 5 &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Full day in the Maasai Mara with morning and afternoon Game viewing drives or an optional full day tour.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	All meals and overnight at SAROVA MARA CAMP (FB).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(The Maasai Mara at 1560sq km is part of the larger Mara-serengeti eco-system. During the months of July/August, close to 2 million wilderbeeste and Zebras cross over the Mara River from Tanzania in search of pasture. The sight of these magnificent herbivores is breathtaking.As is, the Mara has the highest concentration of Lions in the country.)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Day 6 &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Breakfast at the lodge. Depart for Nairobi to arrive in the early afternoon. Lunch at a Chinese Restaurant.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Panaroma city tour of Nairobi to include shopping.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Later transfer to the airport for your onward flight.</p>\r\n', 23, 2, '', 'en', '', '', ''),
